Natural All Purpose Cleaning Solution

1. Heat lemon slices in 2 cups of water at 220 degrees for 20 minutes
2. Pour water to fill 75% of your glass spray bottle
3. Pour in 1 cup of vinegar into your glass spray bottle
4. Add 10-20 drops of essential oil (i.e. Eucalyptus, Tea Tree, Lavender)
5. Optional: Cut the heated lemons vertically and add them into your bottle (be sure to cut them thin so when it’s time to rinse your bottle, it easily slip out of the bottle opening)
6. Mix all ingredients in the spray bottle
7. Shake Well before use
Streamline your morning with these 5 simple tips you can do every night. Happy Homemaking! 🧺

DIY TOXIN FREE FLOOR CLEANER (concentrate) 

For Hardwood Floors: 
1/2 capful Thieves Cleaner 
1 Tsp Vinegar 
2 Tbsp Olive Oil
5 Drops (or more) of Essential Oils

Combine this with 4 cups of hot water to mop about 400 square feet.

For Tile & Linoleum:
1/2 Capful Thieves Cleaner 
1/2 Cup of Vinegar
1/2 Cup Rubbing Alcohol
5 Drops (or more) of Essential Oils

Combine with 4 cups of hot water to mop about 409 square feet (or about 4 medium-sized rooms). #homemaking #homeremedy

How to include your child in the kitchen. 

Here are 3 very simple ways to include your child in the kitchen: 

1. Buy kid-safe tools like these serrated edge plastic knives so they can help themselves with simply tasks. 

2. Designate a drawer your child can easily pull and put all their essentials, keep it simple and neat. Don’t overcrowd as they will be overstimulated. This is essentially important for toddlers as this drawer helps in communicating when they are hungry. 

3. Have a simple trash can they can open and close with ease to throw away any left overs from their plates before they put the plates in the sink. 

Including your child in the kitchen supports their confidence , independence and gives them a sense of responsibility by allowing them to make little decisions and creating an environment they can maneuver in freely. #homemaking #motherhoodunplugged #kidsinthekitchen

Benefits of Grounding

Grounding for only an hour a day can have a significant positive impact on our mind, body and soul. Try it! Walk on the ground barefoot, have your feet touch the soil directly, your body will absorb negative electrons from the earth. The negative ions help balance the positive ions in your body and improve your health.

Walking without shoes helps boost immunity, glucose regulation, improve skin conductivity, reduce stress and anxiety and check heart rate variability. It stabilizes our cortisol circadian rhythm to balance our internal bioelectrical environment. 

Grounding activates the pressure points in the feet similar to acupuncture. It makes us feel more energized and studies have found that grounding positively changes the electrical activity in your brain which is gauged by electroencephalograms. #grounding #wellness #earthing #earthing👣

How can I create a calm morning routine? 

Say your morning intentions to set the mood for the rest of your day. Be tech-free for at least 1 hour after you wake up. Schedule your wake up time before the kids. Prep some breakfast meals the night before. Use visual schedules especially if you are a visual learner. 

#morningroutine #calmmorning

Close-knit siblings have families with strong mental health. A study from the University of Nebraska, on the characteristics of strong families, recognized six major qualities that strong families share. 

These qualities contributed to the happiness and strength of the family:

1. Commitment- family members put each other first
2. Appreciation- regularly show they appreciate each other
3. Communication- talk about both big and small issues openly
4. Time together– make time to spend with each other 
5. Spiritual wellness– have similar values and beliefs
6. Crisis and stress– can cope with problems and challenges

#siblings ##homemaker #childhoodmemories #family #mentalhealth
